Re: Major Meltdown

Bitcointalk

2010-07-10 13:36:17 UTC - [11]Original Post

   [12]Quote from: llama on July 01, 2010, 10:21:47 PM
   However, if something happened and the signatures were compromised
   (perhaps integer factorization is solved, quantum computers?), then
   even agreeing upon the last valid block would be worthless.
   True, if it happened suddenly.  If it happens gradually, we can still
   transition to something stronger.  When you run the upgraded software
   for the first time, it would re-sign all your money with the new
   stronger signature algorithm.  (by creating a transaction sending the
   money to yourself with the stronger sig)
